               <floruit notBefore="1398" notAfter="1438">He was a 14th century metropolitan of the Ethiopian Orthodox Church who arrived in <date> 1398/99</date> 
                  after ten year vacancy of the episcopal seat at <placeName ref="LOC1311AksumS">ʾAksum Ṣǝyon</placeName>. His episcopate covered the lengthy period  
                  from the end of the reign of King <persName ref="PRS3429DawitII">Dāwit I</persName> and the entire reign of King <persName ref="PRS10342Yeshaq">Yǝsḥaq</persName>. 
                  He was the successor of ʾabuna <persName ref="PRS8387SalamaI">Salāmā II “The Translator”</persName>. 
                   </floruit>
